3
00:00:08,041 --> 00:00:10,041
[ominous music playing]

4
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:56,250
[ominous music intensifies]

5
00:01:29,333 --> 00:01:32,707
[man on comm] <i>Good copy, Sapper Patrol.
You're exiting the green zone now.</i>

6
00:01:32,708 --> 00:01:35,624
<i>10th Mountain's convoy
is stranded, no sitrep.</i>

7
00:01:35,625 --> 00:01:38,415
<i>Be advised,
Spartans convoy is in a black spot.</i>

8
00:01:38,416 --> 00:01:40,790
<i>Comms will be sketchy.
Stay sharp, watch your six.</i>

9
00:01:40,791 --> 00:01:41,791
[comm chirps]

10
00:01:45,083 --> 00:01:47,083
[ominous music continues]

11
00:01:49,541 --> 00:01:51,541
[soldiers chattering indistinctly]

12
00:02:03,916 --> 00:02:05,916
[music fades]

13
00:02:07,750 --> 00:02:11,000
Who's the full-fledged moron
responsible for this clusterfuck?

14
00:02:13,625 --> 00:02:15,915
Who's the meathead calling me a moron?

15
00:02:15,916 --> 00:02:18,499
Meathead? You fucked up my morning pass.

16
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:21,083
- Oh, what are you gonna do about it?
- What am I gonna do?

17
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,457
Noogie, baby! Got you again.

18
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:26,707
[both laughing]

19
00:02:26,708 --> 00:02:29,875
- Wait, you know this guy?
- This one? Nah, never met him.

20
00:02:30,625 --> 00:02:33,458
I just have the exact same tattoo
by coincidence.

21
00:02:35,916 --> 00:02:37,165
Really?

22
00:02:37,166 --> 00:02:39,125
He's my big brother, numbnuts.

23
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:41,625
- Good to see you, bro.
- You too.

24
00:02:42,416 --> 00:02:43,540
[older brother grunts]

25
00:02:43,541 --> 00:02:45,125
[jets roaring overhead]

26
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:48,374
- What'd this idiot do?
- I don't know.

27
00:02:48,375 --> 00:02:50,875
Hey, Tommy, a bit of hospitality.
Get the shit.

28
00:02:52,958 --> 00:02:55,540
[brother] Let me give you a science lesson
on the laws of physics.

29
00:02:55,541 --> 00:02:57,916
Walk you through
what you should have learned in 8th grade.

30
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,624
First law of thermodynamics.

31
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:03,708
Energy can't be created or destroyed,
so it's gotta go somewhere.

32
00:03:04,375 --> 00:03:07,790
When you idiots fill these trucks
with Stop Leak, you block the vents.

33
00:03:07,791 --> 00:03:11,249
Heat can't escape.
Pressure builds till the radiator blows.

34
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:12,416
You listening to this, Tommy?

35
00:03:14,541 --> 00:03:16,082
[softly] Get that shit out of here.

36
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:17,790
I know it was you.

37
00:03:17,791 --> 00:03:19,750
Mechanics keep ratting you out.

38
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:23,415
Why do you do it?

39
00:03:23,416 --> 00:03:25,582
- You just don't care?
- No, I care.

40
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:27,540
Sure, I care about this fucking golf cart

41
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:30,207
I get to drive around the desert
breaking down every five minutes.

42
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:32,999
- Your fault.
- Man, we should be on the front lines.

43
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,250
Fucking kicking doors
like we said when we joined.

44
00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:37,749
You know, we were all,
"Don't fucking quit."

45
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,249
What'd we do? We fucking quit.

46
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:40,625
Dude, what are you talking about?

47
00:03:41,208 --> 00:03:45,874
I'm talking about
Ranger Assessment Selection Program.

48
00:03:45,875 --> 00:03:47,499
[poignant music playing]

49
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,665
My God.

50
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:50,499
- RASP?
- [younger brother] Yeah.

51
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,583
Dude, take Tommy.

52
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:54,416
Tommy? He can't even spell "Ranger."

53
00:03:55,166 --> 00:03:56,790
Intake starts in June.

54
00:03:56,791 --> 00:03:58,375
That ship has sailed.

55
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:02,333
Rangers are fucking hardcore.

56
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,040
I'm fucking old.

57
00:04:04,041 --> 00:04:06,707
- You're fucking ugly.
- No, I checked the cutoff. We're good.

58
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:09,457
Bro, you wanna be a Ranger,
go be a Ranger.

59
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:10,708
You don't need my permission.

60
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:14,750
I wanted to do it together, you know?

61
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:17,000
Like we promised each other.

62
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:20,000
Bro, we were 18.

63
00:04:21,125 --> 00:04:23,165
We also said
we were gonna start a thrash band.

64
00:04:23,166 --> 00:04:25,499
Come on, man, just imagine.

65
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:29,040
You and me, getting our Ranger Scrolls.

66
00:04:29,041 --> 00:04:31,624
Fucking running across the tarmac.
Black Hawks.

67
00:04:31,625 --> 00:04:33,541
First boots on the ground.

68
00:04:35,916 --> 00:04:36,958
[chuckles]

69
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:42,000
- That does sound pretty awesome.
- Yeah.

70
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:44,666
[laughs]

71
00:04:46,041 --> 00:04:48,333
All right. You're in, I'm in.

72
00:04:49,291 --> 00:04:50,125
You promise?

73
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:52,541
Always.

74
00:04:55,791 --> 00:04:57,041
Unbelievable.

75
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,874
- I just gotta top it off with coolant.
- I got that shit.

76
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:03,083
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, get outta here!

77
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:07,791
[groans] I don't see you
screwing this up at all.

78
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,624
Hey, Tom, fill it up.

79
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:14,332
- We're both gonna be badass Army Rangers!
- Starting to regret saying yes already.

80
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:15,999
- Tier one, baby!
- [laughs]

81
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,749
Hey, you're not gonna say goodbye?

82
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:20,457
I'll see you tomorrow
when you fill it up again with Stop Leak.

83
00:05:20,458 --> 00:05:22,249
We're gonna be Rangers, baby!

84
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:23,875
[soldier 1] Incoming!

85
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:26,082
- [dramatic music playing]
- [yells]

86
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:28,082
- [soldier 2] Contact!
- [machine guns firing]

87
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:29,500
Mortar incoming!

88
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,125
Get down!

89
00:05:36,166 --> 00:05:39,166
[soldier 3] Go! Get up!

90
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:44,291
[sound fades]

91
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,958
- [unsettling music playing]
- [high-pitched ringing]

92
00:05:56,375 --> 00:05:59,416
[muffled screams]

93
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:06,125
[unsettling music continues]

94
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,583
[yells]

95
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:27,333
[gasping]

96
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,790
- [gasps]
- [music fades]

97
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:33,791
[breathing heavily]

98
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:41,958
[wistful music playing]

99
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,374
[music turns ominous]

100
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:52,749
[cadre 1] Five minutes to base.

101
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:54,708
Get your packs ready!

102
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,833
[music turns dramatic]

103
00:07:21,958 --> 00:07:25,499
[cadre 2] Welcome to
the Ranger Assessment Selection Program!

104
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:31,624
All candidates must proceed at pace
to the induction hall immediately!

105
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:32,540
[cadre 3] Move!

106
00:07:32,541 --> 00:07:34,290
[cadre 2] You will receive a Ziploc bag.

107
00:07:34,291 --> 00:07:37,874
Place your name, paper,
and rank inside that Ziploc bag.

108
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:40,707
- Anything personal, hand it over.
- [cadre 3] Tuck in your shirt!

109
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:42,749
[cadre 2] Jewelry, phones, wallets, meds.

110
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,582
You no longer have a name.

111
00:07:44,583 --> 00:07:45,790
You are a number!

112
00:07:45,791 --> 00:07:47,415
You are now number 44.

113
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:48,375
Next!

114
00:07:49,166 --> 00:07:52,207
- You are now number 198.
- [cadres yelling indistinctly]

115
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:54,249
- [cadre 4] 190.
- [soldier] Yes, sir.

116
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:56,832
As an E-6, you'll be assigned team leader.

117
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:59,165
- State your consent.
- Yes, Sergeant.

118
00:07:59,166 --> 00:08:00,500
You're now number 7.

119
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:02,957
[cadre 4] Look who's back.

120
00:08:02,958 --> 00:08:05,665
- One strike and you'll be out again.
- If I may say so, Sergeant--

121
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:07,000
- Shut the fuck up.
- Yeah.

122
00:08:07,583 --> 00:08:10,124
You are now number 15. Next!

123
00:08:10,125 --> 00:08:12,165
You are now number 111.

124
00:08:12,166 --> 00:08:13,625
[cadre 4] Number 122.

125
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:17,999
Fuck me. Applied four times,
medically denied each time.

126
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,999
But he just made the age cutoff.

127
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,375
You got a plan B?

128
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:23,540
No, Sergeant.

129
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:25,249
[dramatic music playing]

130
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:28,124
As an E-6,
you will be assigned team leader.

131
00:08:28,125 --> 00:08:29,499
State your consent.

132
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:30,500
I'd rather not.

133
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:34,333
[cadre 2] Ten minutes to formation!

134
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,041
You are now number 81.

135
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:40,249
- Yes, Sergeant.
- [cadre 2] Ten minutes to formation!

136
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:43,665
Rangers are the spearhead
of the United States Army.

137
00:08:43,666 --> 00:08:46,957
We are first on the ground
every single time.

138
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:51,040
{\an8}The fate of our nation and allies
depends on our expertise.

139
00:08:51,041 --> 00:08:52,249
{\an8}Do you understand me?

140
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:54,166
[in unison] Yes, First Sergeant!

141
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:56,915
[First Sergeant]
You are about to embark on eight weeks

142
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:59,665
of the hardest selection program
in the world.

143
00:08:59,666 --> 00:09:04,082
Whether you have been deployed in combat
or you are fresh out of basic,

144
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:07,665
you can expect your emotional,
physical, and mental strength

145
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:10,624
to be pushed to the absolute limit
and then some.

146
00:09:10,625 --> 00:09:14,499
If, by the grace of God,
you make it to the final stage,

147
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:17,415
you will undertake
a 24-hour simulated mission

148
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:19,457
known as Death March,

149
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:22,999
completed by crossing that finish line.

150
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,583
[dramatic music continues]

151
00:09:26,541 --> 00:09:32,374
At which point you will be eligible
for the Ranger Scroll, the tan beret,

152
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:35,666
and the most storied regiment
in the United States Army.

153
00:09:37,125 --> 00:09:39,208
Attention!

154
00:09:39,708 --> 00:09:41,207
Rangers lead the way!

155
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:42,540
[in unison] All the way!

156
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:44,124
[First Sergeant] Welcome to RASP!

157
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:47,665
[cadre 1] Come on, candidate!
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

158
00:09:47,666 --> 00:09:49,290
[cadre 2] Let's see what you got!

159
00:09:49,291 --> 00:09:51,332
Tough it out! Let's go!

160
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:54,082
[First Sergeant]
<i>We are looking for elite warriors!</i>

161
00:09:54,083 --> 00:09:56,332
<i>The best of the best.</i>

162
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:58,749
[cadre 3] Seventeen,
get the fuck out of here!

163
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:01,915
[First Sergeant] <i>Every week,
those who fail will be eliminated.</i>

164
00:10:01,916 --> 00:10:03,415
[cadre 4] We just fucking started!

165
00:10:03,416 --> 00:10:07,749
[First Sergeant]
16, 27, 29, 53, step forward.

166
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:10,624
- Pack your bags. You are non-selects.
- [cadre 5] Get out.

167
00:10:10,625 --> 00:10:12,499
- [cadre 6] Come on, 81!
- [soldiers] 38.

168
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:13,333
[cadre 6] Down!

169
00:10:14,083 --> 00:10:15,082
Up!

170
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:16,999
- [soldiers] Thirty-nine!
- [cadre 6] Down!

171
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:17,915
[soldiers] Forty!

172
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:20,749
[First Sergeant] If you're thinking
about quitting, do it now.

173
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:22,541
[dramatic music continues]

174
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:27,665
<i>- Welcome to week three.</i>
- [grunts]

175
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,457
[First Sergeant] <i>The culling of the herd.</i>

176
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:31,624
This one's broken, get him out of here!

177
00:10:31,625 --> 00:10:32,874
[cadre 2] Pick up those feet!

178
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,915
[First Sergeant]
<i>There's no shame in quitting.</i>

179
00:10:34,916 --> 00:10:36,582
<i>Most of you will quit.</i>

180
00:10:36,583 --> 00:10:38,957
[cadre 6] Do you really
have what it takes?

181
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:40,208
Rangers lead the way!

182
00:10:41,791 --> 00:10:47,082
[First Sergeant]
77, 84, 142, step forward.

183
00:10:47,083 --> 00:10:49,207
{\an8}You are non-selects. Pack your bags.

184
00:10:49,208 --> 00:10:51,583
[dramatic music continues]

185
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:56,374
[cadre 4 over bullhorn]
Four weeks down! Four weeks to go!

186
00:10:56,375 --> 00:10:57,707
You made it halfway.

187
00:10:57,708 --> 00:11:01,791
But if you think it gets any easier,
you are wrong!

188
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:09,082
I'm just saying, once we join regiment,
it's top-secret clearance, right?

189
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:11,624
Means they're gonna have to
tell us the truth about some things.

190
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:15,832
Y'all know what I'm talking about.
I'm talking Area 51, moon landings.

191
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:18,040
I'm talking Tupac. Come on.

192
00:11:18,041 --> 00:11:19,415
You're talking shit.

193
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:23,041
You think they're just gonna hand over
an envelope of secrets with your scroll?

194
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:25,915
- [15] Hell yeah.
- [44] That's not how it works, bro.

195
00:11:25,916 --> 00:11:28,165
[15] Oh, and how would you know that, 44?

196
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:30,415
I was DOD. I had the clearance.

197
00:11:30,416 --> 00:11:33,707
Real question is why they gave us
rifles with blanks in them

198
00:11:33,708 --> 00:11:36,165
when you can bet
there's some good hunting up here.

199
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:37,290
Yeah.

200
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:39,082
'Cause otherwise we'd all shoot 15.

201
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:41,124
[laughing]

202
00:11:41,125 --> 00:11:42,290
[15] Very funny, 7.

203
00:11:42,291 --> 00:11:43,250
[cadre 1] Look out.

204
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:45,500
[cadre 4] Here comes the first.

205
00:11:46,916 --> 00:11:48,707
[cadre 1]
Where's everyone else, candidate?

206
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,125
Behind me, Sarge.

207
00:11:52,208 --> 00:11:53,208
[stopwatch beeps]

208
00:11:56,791 --> 00:11:58,165
[15] Hey, slow down, Superman.

209
00:11:58,166 --> 00:12:00,166
Making the rest of us look bad.

210
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:04,250
[indistinct chatter and laughter]

211
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:12,958
- [dramatic music playing]
- [soldiers yelling and cheering]

212
00:12:17,458 --> 00:12:18,832
[cheering and whistling]

213
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,000
[grunting]

214
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:22,582
[whistle blows]

215
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:25,082
[cadre 4] That is exactly
what I was talking about.

216
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:27,457
[cadre 2] Now, we got a lot
of hopped-up 11 Bravos

217
00:12:27,458 --> 00:12:28,957
who know how to shoot a rifle,

218
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:32,624
but I want a show of hands
who's actually been deployed.

219
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:34,916
Where'd you serve, 109?

220
00:12:35,416 --> 00:12:38,165
Fort Benning, Sergeant.
Basic, AIT, and airborne.

221
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:39,374
Honor grad. Top of the class.

222
00:12:39,375 --> 00:12:42,374
Deployments, candidate,
not potty training.

223
00:12:42,375 --> 00:12:44,040
And what about you, 60?

224
00:12:44,041 --> 00:12:46,374
19-Kilo, M1 Abrams crewman, Sergeant.

225
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:48,290
Hot damn, a tanker.

226
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:51,665
- Maybe you can valet my Lambo.
- [soldiers laugh]

227
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:52,874
What about you, 81?

228
00:12:52,875 --> 00:12:56,582
12 Bravo, combat engineer, 213th CSSB.

229
00:12:56,583 --> 00:12:58,540
Who were you supporting, Sapper?

230
00:12:58,541 --> 00:12:59,625
Third Brigade.

231
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:01,750
10th Mountain Division.

232
00:13:02,458 --> 00:13:03,415
Spartans.

233
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:05,249
[soldiers whisper indistinctly]

234
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:07,500
[dramatic music continues]

235
00:13:09,916 --> 00:13:11,083
All right.

236
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,416
Let's see what you got.

237
00:13:17,083 --> 00:13:18,375
[cadre 7] Ready! Up!

238
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:21,125
Ready! Up!

239
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:28,457
- What happened to him?
- 213th was helping a stranded convoy.

240
00:13:28,458 --> 00:13:30,958
Taliban showed up
and smoked the whole unit.

241
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:32,999
[60] Holy shit.

242
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,665
That's him.

243
00:13:34,666 --> 00:13:37,125
- I heard he got a Silver Star.
- What?

244
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:38,957
No shit.

245
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:42,040
[woman on TV] <i>NASA has detected
a massive interstellar object</i>

246
00:13:42,041 --> 00:13:44,832
<i>believed to originate
from outside our solar system,</i>

247
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:46,415
<i>projected to pass by Earth…</i>

248
00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:48,832
You probably think
NASA's making that shit up too.

249
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,957
{\an8}<i>Although it'll transit
close to Earth's orbit,</i>

250
00:13:50,958 --> 00:13:53,207
{\an8}<i>officials say there is no cause for alarm.</i>

251
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:54,166
Yeah.

252
00:13:54,791 --> 00:13:56,333
[tense music playing]

253
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:02,207
{\an8}146, 148, 149, step forward!

254
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:04,625
Pack your bags. You are non-selects.

255
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:11,249
You're telling me that guy
won a Silver fucking Star?

256
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:12,250
That's what I heard.

257
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:16,124
They say the only survivor carried
his brother ten miles back to base.

258
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:17,999
Wait. His actual brother?

259
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,583
That's what they said.

260
00:14:20,708 --> 00:14:22,083
Hey, 81.

261
00:14:22,666 --> 00:14:25,625
- Is it true what happened in Kandahar?
- [7] Fifteen.

262
00:14:26,208 --> 00:14:29,125
- Mind your business, man.
- I just wanna know if he's a hero or not.

263
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,290
Who the fuck is talking in the DFAC?

264
00:14:32,291 --> 00:14:34,332
Don't tell me that was you, 15.

265
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:36,166
You looking to recycle again?

266
00:14:37,958 --> 00:14:39,041
It was me, Sergeant.

267
00:14:40,083 --> 00:14:40,999
[sergeant] Bullshit!

268
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,457
Extra hill climb!

269
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,624
Everyone, thank 15!

270
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:45,708
[soldiers groan]

271
00:14:49,291 --> 00:14:51,540
Forty-four, why are you here?

272
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:53,290
To fight with the best!

273
00:14:53,291 --> 00:14:54,832
[cadre 1] Sixty, why are you here?

274
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:56,499
To serve in an elite unit!

275
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,666
Eighty-one, why are you here?

276
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,875
To cross that finish line.

277
00:15:02,708 --> 00:15:05,415
[First Sergeant]
<i>This is not just a physical test.</i>

278
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:08,374
<i>This is a mental and emotional test.</i>

279
00:15:08,375 --> 00:15:11,124
<i>If you cannot control what's inside,</i>

280
00:15:11,125 --> 00:15:13,832
<i>you will not control what's outside.</i>

281
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:15,833
[poignant, pensive music playing]

282
00:15:28,916 --> 00:15:31,415
- [soldiers grunting]
- [whistle blows]

283
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:33,124
[cadre 2] Thirty-second break!

284
00:15:33,125 --> 00:15:35,125
- [soldiers gasping]
- [music fades]

285
00:15:42,416 --> 00:15:44,416
[dramatic music playing]

286
00:15:46,166 --> 00:15:47,124
[gasps]

287
00:15:47,125 --> 00:15:48,457
[7] D.F.Q.?

288
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:50,291
Don't Fucking Quit, right?

289
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:53,415
How'd you know that?

290
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:55,540
[whistle blows]

291
00:15:55,541 --> 00:15:56,416
Lucky guess.

292
00:15:57,083 --> 00:16:00,165
[cadre 2] All right, people,
we are back! Let's go! Let's go!

293
00:16:00,166 --> 00:16:02,499
Come on, candidates! This ain't recess.

294
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:05,166
Come on, 15, move it out! Let's go!

295
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:08,749
[cadre 8] Breach! Breach! Breach!

296
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:10,290
[dramatic music playing]

297
00:16:10,291 --> 00:16:11,291
[81] Clear!

298
00:16:11,875 --> 00:16:15,915
This is week six! You'll be abseiling
on a figure-eight device!

299
00:16:15,916 --> 00:16:18,291
This shit will save your life.

300
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:23,749
[First Sergeant]
65, 48, and 143, step forward!

301
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,625
{\an8}Pack your bags, you are non-selects!

302
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:30,041
[soldier 1] Come on! Cover me!

303
00:16:30,875 --> 00:16:32,374
Move! Move! Move!

304
00:16:32,375 --> 00:16:33,291
[soldier 2] Move it!

305
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:34,915
[soldier 1] Covering!

306
00:16:34,916 --> 00:16:35,999
Run!

307
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,832
[soldier 1] Move it! Quick!

308
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:39,083
Move! Move! Move!

309
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:42,458
[Spartan soldier] <i>Incoming!</i>

310
00:16:44,416 --> 00:16:45,332
[gasps]

311
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,415
[breathing heavily]

312
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:49,499
[unsettling music playing]

313
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:50,583
[door opens]

314
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:54,958
Wake up, assholes!
Welcome to the final week.

315
00:16:56,708 --> 00:16:59,207
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

316
00:16:59,208 --> 00:17:02,208
It's a glorious day to become a Ranger.

317
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,333
[tense music playing]

318
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:09,000
[soldiers cheering and applauding]

319
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:22,082
[cadre 2] Fifty-seven, out of my pool!

320
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:24,790
- Fifteen, out! Forty-four, out!
- Shit!

321
00:17:24,791 --> 00:17:26,791
[determined music playing]

322
00:17:32,916 --> 00:17:33,958
I'm here!

323
00:17:34,791 --> 00:17:37,750
- All right. Stay with me!
- [emotional music playing]

324
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:42,500
Stay with me. Please.

325
00:17:53,083 --> 00:17:54,333
Hang in there!

326
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,500
[groaning]

327
00:18:07,958 --> 00:18:11,208
Stay with me. I got you. Breathe!

328
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:18,625
[yelling]

329
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:32,750
- [cadres grunt]
- [music fades]

330
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:36,166
[cadre 9] Jeez. [grunting]

331
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:43,540
[cadre 9 grunting]

332
00:18:43,541 --> 00:18:46,624
- [sighs]
- [coughing]

333
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:49,333
Sapper, you are officially
one crazy motherfucker.

334
00:18:53,625 --> 00:18:55,915
[Sergeant Major] He's a liability.

335
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:58,207
I want to see him in my office.

336
00:18:58,208 --> 00:19:00,290
[ominous music playing]

337
00:19:00,291 --> 00:19:02,291
[gasping]

338
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:12,290
[man on TV] <i>The asteroid
discovered last month</i>

339
00:19:12,291 --> 00:19:14,499
<i>continues to confound scientists</i>

340
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:17,915
<i>as it now shows signs
of structural fragmentation</i>

341
00:19:17,916 --> 00:19:19,875
<i>with uniform sections splitting apart.</i>

342
00:19:20,583 --> 00:19:24,624
<i>Some experts believe
it may not be a single object at all,</i>

343
00:19:24,625 --> 00:19:28,374
<i>but rather a cluster
of smaller interstellar bodies…</i>

344
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:30,375
[ominous music intensifies]

345
00:19:31,458 --> 00:19:33,874
- [music stops]
- [First Sergeant] Come on in, candidate.

346
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:36,041
<i>The situation is being closely monitored.</i>

347
00:19:37,916 --> 00:19:41,499
Unfortunately, First Sergeant Torres and I
are going to recommend

348
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:44,833
that you retire from the course,
effective immediately.

349
00:19:45,416 --> 00:19:46,415
You're done.

350
00:19:46,416 --> 00:19:47,790
- I'm done?
- [Torres] Sit down.

351
00:19:47,791 --> 00:19:50,541
- On what grounds?!
- Sit down, soldier!

352
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:55,415
Sergeant Major,
I haven't failed an event yet.

353
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:58,082
Your physical strength is not in question.

354
00:19:58,083 --> 00:20:01,000
What concerns us
is what's going on inside your head.

355
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:04,665
Cadre says you're not sleeping.

356
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:07,749
Peer review indicates you're not bonding
with the other candidates.

357
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:09,415
And I've known since day one

358
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,958
you've ducked every single opportunity
to be a team leader.

359
00:20:12,583 --> 00:20:14,874
These aren't the hallmarks
of a stable candidate.

360
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,332
[Sergeant Major] No, they're not.

361
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:21,083
Usually, when a soldier goes
through a world of shit like you have,

362
00:20:21,666 --> 00:20:24,832
they take a little time off, recuperate,

363
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:31,125
maybe attend at least one of those
VA-recommended group therapy sessions.

364
00:20:33,958 --> 00:20:35,416
But you didn't do that.

365
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:41,290
What your record says is that
the very morning of your discharge,

366
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:43,457
you applied for RASP.

367
00:20:43,458 --> 00:20:44,832
And, in fact, since then,

368
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:50,250
repeatedly applying for RASP
seems to be the only thing you've done.

369
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,000
Now, why is that?

370
00:20:55,125 --> 00:20:58,166
I just want to get across
that finish line, Sergeant Major.

371
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:04,458
That finish line is a starting line.

372
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,333
[Sergeant Major] Son,

373
00:21:09,916 --> 00:21:11,916
I'm gonna be honest with you.

374
00:21:13,666 --> 00:21:17,040
You're one of the most promising
candidates we've ever seen.

375
00:21:17,041 --> 00:21:20,916
And Sergeant Torres and I
think you have a lot of potential.

376
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:26,791
Truth is, we could kick you out
right here, right now.

377
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:30,291
But there'd be no coming back.

378
00:21:31,125 --> 00:21:32,125
So, instead,

379
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:34,499
what I have here

380
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:36,958
is a voluntary quit slip.

381
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:41,665
Now, I want you to do yourself a favor
and sign it.

382
00:21:41,666 --> 00:21:43,999
[somber music playing]

383
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,874
You're an engineer.

384
00:21:45,875 --> 00:21:48,790
So you know
even the most powerful machines

385
00:21:48,791 --> 00:21:50,291
have their limits.

386
00:21:52,041 --> 00:21:54,583
And I think you've reached yours.

387
00:22:10,375 --> 00:22:11,875
If you don't mind…

388
00:22:15,750 --> 00:22:17,916
I'd like to go prep for parade now.

389
00:22:19,666 --> 00:22:21,666
[music fades]

390
00:22:22,666 --> 00:22:25,291
You get the fuck out of my office.

391
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,416
[door opens]

392
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,000
[door closes]

393
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:38,332
How do you want to play this?

394
00:22:38,333 --> 00:22:40,333
[ominous music playing]

395
00:22:42,916 --> 00:22:46,958
[Torres] 38, 44, 57,

396
00:22:47,958 --> 00:22:49,000
Sixty,

397
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:51,457
Eighty-one,

398
00:22:51,458 --> 00:22:56,958
96, 109, 111, step forward.

399
00:22:59,875 --> 00:23:02,749
I'm sorry to say that those of you
who did not step forward,

400
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:05,374
pack your bags, you are non-selects.

401
00:23:05,375 --> 00:23:07,375
[dramatic music playing]

402
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:12,790
To those who stepped forward, congratulations.

403
00:23:12,791 --> 00:23:14,415
You made it through to the final round.

404
00:23:14,416 --> 00:23:17,707
You have 30 minutes to gear up
and get ready for one final test

405
00:23:17,708 --> 00:23:20,457
to see if you have what it takes
to be a Ranger.

406
00:23:20,458 --> 00:23:23,374
- You are dismissed.
- Mama-say mama-sa, motherfucker!

407
00:23:23,375 --> 00:23:24,374
Let's go!

408
00:23:24,375 --> 00:23:25,832
[both yell]

409
00:23:25,833 --> 00:23:26,915
[60] Let's go!

410
00:23:26,916 --> 00:23:28,208
[whooping and cheering]

411
00:23:30,125 --> 00:23:33,708
[music crescendos, then fades]

412
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,625
[Torres] All right, listen up.
Here's the situation.

413
00:23:37,208 --> 00:23:40,707
Got a classified aircraft
shot down behind enemy lines.

414
00:23:40,708 --> 00:23:43,457
Rangers are tasked with recon and rescue.

415
00:23:43,458 --> 00:23:47,624
Two Black Hawks are gonna carry you down
to your drop zone deep in enemy territory.

416
00:23:47,625 --> 00:23:50,665
You'll then maneuver
toward the downed aircraft's position.

417
00:23:50,666 --> 00:23:54,499
You need to destroy the aircraft
so it doesn't fall into enemy hands.

418
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:56,083
But we'll provide you extra C4.

419
00:23:56,916 --> 00:24:01,499
Next, locate the rebel village outpost
where the pilot of the downed aircraft

420
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:03,290
is being held as a POW.

421
00:24:03,291 --> 00:24:08,082
You can expect perimeter surveillance
and 360 security.

422
00:24:08,083 --> 00:24:11,749
Your rifles have blank-firing adapters,
so you can't shoot.

423
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:15,165
But be warned,
you may be ambushed by cadre at any time.

424
00:24:15,166 --> 00:24:17,540
Your squad will be equipped
with a single VHF

425
00:24:17,541 --> 00:24:19,749
to provide round-the-clock sitreps.

426
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:21,875
Apart from that, you're on your own.

427
00:24:22,583 --> 00:24:23,708
Team Leader 7,

428
00:24:24,708 --> 00:24:26,125
you're now 2IC.

429
00:24:26,666 --> 00:24:28,833
And your new team leader will be

430
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:30,707
Eighty-one.

431
00:24:30,708 --> 00:24:32,750
[dramatic music playing]

432
00:24:34,875 --> 00:24:37,375
Great. Mr. Finish Line.

433
00:24:37,958 --> 00:24:40,374
[Torres] You will bring the pilot
back to base camp

434
00:24:40,375 --> 00:24:42,915
and cross that finish line by 1900.

435
00:24:42,916 --> 00:24:46,958
If at any point during this exercise
you are successfully ambushed,

436
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,666
the mission's over, and you have failed.

437
00:24:52,208 --> 00:24:54,874
[Sergeant Major]
And <i>if</i> you cross that line,

438
00:24:54,875 --> 00:25:01,624
{\an8}I will personally award you
the US Army Ranger Regiment Scroll.

439
00:25:01,625 --> 00:25:03,791
Welcome to Death March.

440
00:25:04,291 --> 00:25:06,083
[dramatic music continues]

441
00:25:14,541 --> 00:25:17,000
You still think this is a good idea?

442
00:25:17,583 --> 00:25:21,333
He wants to be a Ranger,
he's gonna have to lead.

443
00:25:23,583 --> 00:25:26,250
[man on comm] <i>Ghost 1, Ghost 2,
you are cleared hot for departure.</i>

444
00:25:28,125 --> 00:25:31,165
- [pilot 1] <i>Ghost 1, lifting.</i>
- [pilot 2] <i>Copy. Ghost 2, lifting.</i>

445
00:25:31,166 --> 00:25:32,958
<i>Staying tight on your six.</i>

446
00:25:40,208 --> 00:25:43,958
[pilot 1] <i>Passing Angels 2.
Leveling at 150 feet AGL.</i>

447
00:25:44,791 --> 00:25:46,750
[pilot 2] <i>Copy. Matching altitude.</i>

448
00:25:52,875 --> 00:25:56,290
How much of this shit you think we rucked
in the last eight weeks?

449
00:25:56,291 --> 00:25:58,833
Everything except whatever that is.

450
00:26:00,125 --> 00:26:01,290
[loadmaster] Private quarry.

451
00:26:01,291 --> 00:26:04,416
You boys come across that,
you are way off course.

452
00:26:04,916 --> 00:26:06,916
[ominous music playing]

453
00:26:18,041 --> 00:26:19,875
[pilot 2 on comm] <i>Thirty seconds out.</i>

454
00:26:22,958 --> 00:26:25,290
We have visual on LZ.

455
00:26:25,291 --> 00:26:27,291
[ominous music continues]

456
00:26:31,458 --> 00:26:33,207
Ropes! Ropes!

457
00:26:33,208 --> 00:26:36,791
[loadmaster] Rope's out!
Green light! Drop! Drop! Drop!

458
00:26:45,625 --> 00:26:48,458
[pilot 1] <i>Chalk 1 down.
Ghost 1 up, shifting to cover.</i>

459
00:26:49,750 --> 00:26:51,333
Go! Go! Go!

460
00:26:55,291 --> 00:26:58,208
[pilot 1] <i>Half team down.
Last sticks moving.</i>

461
00:26:59,166 --> 00:27:00,666
[music turns dramatic]

462
00:27:02,791 --> 00:27:05,166
All right, let's go!

463
00:27:07,708 --> 00:27:09,665
[pilot 2] <i>Ghost 2 to GUC Command.</i>

464
00:27:09,666 --> 00:27:12,332
<i>Drop clean. Death March is in effect.</i>

465
00:27:12,333 --> 00:27:15,540
<i>I repeat, Death March is in effect.</i>

466
00:27:15,541 --> 00:27:17,541
[music fades]

467
00:27:22,083 --> 00:27:24,041
All right, 57. Where we at?

468
00:27:24,958 --> 00:27:26,875
[birds singing and chirping]

469
00:27:29,541 --> 00:27:33,041
Target's that direction, 20 klicks west.

470
00:27:36,750 --> 00:27:38,457
- [81] Okay.
- [beeps]

471
00:27:38,458 --> 00:27:41,249
We got exactly
23 hours, 59 minutes, and 30 seconds

472
00:27:41,250 --> 00:27:42,708
to get across that finish line.

473
00:27:44,666 --> 00:27:45,708
Any questions?

474
00:27:50,375 --> 00:27:52,625
Dude, that was awesome. For real.

475
00:27:53,583 --> 00:27:55,415
I mean, that was like
some <i>Braveheart</i> shit.

476
00:27:55,416 --> 00:27:56,665
That was…

477
00:27:56,666 --> 00:27:57,957
It was inspiring stuff.

478
00:27:57,958 --> 00:27:59,583
Mind if I have a word?

479
00:28:03,708 --> 00:28:05,916
Remember, we're all here for one reason.

480
00:28:06,708 --> 00:28:08,083
We never give up.

481
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:11,166
I'm proud as hell to know
each and every one of y'all.

482
00:28:11,958 --> 00:28:12,957
Even you, 15.

483
00:28:12,958 --> 00:28:14,124
[scattered laughter]

484
00:28:14,125 --> 00:28:15,916
Let's have each other's backs out there.

485
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:19,250
Let's cross that finish line
and get these scrolls together, all right?

486
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:22,749
- Rangers lead the way.
- [in unison] All the way!

487
00:28:22,750 --> 00:28:24,041
All right.

488
00:28:25,166 --> 00:28:26,208
It's all you.

489
00:28:32,125 --> 00:28:33,374
Follow me.

490
00:28:33,375 --> 00:28:35,375
[ominous music playing]

491
00:28:50,958 --> 00:28:52,958
[gasping and grunting]

492
00:29:02,208 --> 00:29:03,041
[groans]

493
00:29:15,750 --> 00:29:19,499
Hotel-9, this is Victor-6.
We've passed phase line red. Over.

494
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:20,665
[music fades]

495
00:29:20,666 --> 00:29:23,290
[cadre 4] <i>Roger, Victor-6.
Phase line red acquired.</i>

496
00:29:23,291 --> 00:29:25,916
We made some good ground.
I think the team could use a rest.

497
00:29:27,416 --> 00:29:30,749
But if Cadre surprises us,
